1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,220
Guys, looks like we'll be approaching
the wormhole in about three hours.

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:09,500
Hey, Coop.

3
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:11,670
Can we stop the spinning?

4
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,500
Why?

5
00:00:13,755 --> 00:00:15,620
Because we're close enough to see him now.

6
00:00:18,140 --> 00:00:19,140
All right.

7
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:20,520
Thanks.

8
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,360
There, that's it. That's the wormhole.

9
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:30,040
You say it don't spread here, huh?

10
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:31,640
It's a sphere.

11
00:00:32,020 --> 00:00:35,140
Of course it is what you
thought it would just be a hole.

12
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,260
No, it's just that all the
illustrations I've ever seen, eh?

13
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:41,560
Illustrations.

14
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:43,080
Let me show you how it works.

15
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:48,200
So they say you want
to go from here to there.

16
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:49,940
But it's too far, right?

17
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:50,820
Mm-hmm.

18
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,660
So a wormhole bends space like this.

19
00:00:53,661 --> 00:00:57,240
So you can take a shortcut
through a higher dimension.

20
00:00:58,260 --> 00:00:58,340
Okay.

21
00:00:58,360 --> 00:01:03,920
Okay, so to show that, they've turned
three-dimensional space into two dimensions,

22
00:01:04,060 --> 00:01:07,280
which turns a wormhole
into two dimensions, a circle.

23
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,780
What's a circle in three dimensions?

24
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:12,300
Sphere.

25
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:13,060
Exactly.

26
00:01:13,660 --> 00:01:14,660
A spherical hole.

27
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,800
But who put it there?

28
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,420
Who do we have to thank?

29
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:22,680
Well, I'm not thanking anybody until
we get out of here in one piece, Rom.

30
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:32,500
A trick to this, Doyle?

31
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:35,840
No one knows.

32
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:44,340
How'd the others made it, right?

33
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:47,740
At least some of them.

